**Reasoning:** The typed component registry and `TState` generic existed at the construction surface but dropped to `Record<string, unknown>` inside callbacks ƒ?" the engine's main authoring surface. Threading them through is mostly mechanical: every `World<TEventMap, TCommandMap>` reference inside callback parameter types becomes `World<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>`. The runtime is identical; this is purely about giving authoring code compile-time access to typed lookups. Per the iter-2 review's tradeoff analysis, the cost is verbosity in advanced signatures and the benefit is real type safety for the most common access pattern (literal-string-key `getComponent`/`getState`).

**Notes:**

- Defaults preserve compatibility: existing System / SystemRegistration / onDestroy / etc. callsites without explicit generics still typecheck because the new generics default to the same `Record<string, unknown>` types the World class uses.
