docs/api-reference.md:3492:`worldWidth`, `worldHeight`, and `blockSize` (default `1`) must be **safe positive integers** (rejected via `Number.isSafeInteger`). The cell grid dimensions are `Math.ceil(worldWidth / blockSize)` × `Math.ceil(worldHeight / blockSize)`; the constructor also rejects dimensions whose product exceeds `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER` to keep cell-index arithmetic exact. `defaultValue` must be JSON-compatible (validated via `assertJsonCompatible`).
docs/api-reference.md:3502:  defaultValue: T;
docs/api-reference.md:3507:Sparse serialization. Only cells whose value differs from `defaultValue` (compared by JSON fingerprint) appear in `cells`; entries are sorted by `cellIndex` for determinism. `cellIndex = cy * width + cx`.
