docs/guides\map-generation.md:466:`Layer<T>` is JSON-serializable via `getState()` / `Layer.fromState()`, value writes are JSON-compat-validated, and reads / writes go through `structuredClone` defensive copies on every boundary so caller mutation cannot corrupt stored state. See [API Reference → Layer](../api-reference.md#layer) for the full surface.
