docs/guides\building-a-game.md:232:For actions where a resource cost and an effect must succeed or fail together (build a building, craft an item, recruit a colonist), `world.transaction()` provides an atomic propose-validate-commit-or-abort builder. The transaction buffers mutations + events + `require()` preconditions; on `commit()` everything applies (preconditions passed) or nothing applies (any precondition failed).
