docs/guides/resources.md:190:### Priority and starvation
docs/guides/resources.md:192:When multiple transfers pull from the same source pool and the pool lacks enough resources to satisfy all of them, the engine processes them in **registration order (FIFO)**. The transfer registered first via `world.addTransfer(...)` drains the source first; later transfers receive only what remains. This is deterministic but can cause silent starvation: a destination registered last gets nothing if earlier transfers exhaust the pool.
