docs\reviews\full\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.stderr.log:1981:1. **Schedule formula corrected** ƒ?" `(tick - 1) % interval === intervalOffset` (was `tick % interval === phaseOffset`). With `interval: N, intervalOffset: 0` the system now fires at ticks 1, N+1, 2N+1 ƒ?" matches the legacy `if (w.tick % N !== 0) return;` schedule by direct substitution. Locked in by the new `matches legacy 'if (w.tick % N !== 0) return;' schedule` parity test that runs both patterns side-by-side and asserts identical fire schedules over 12 steps.
