docs\reviews\full\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.stderr.log:2074:3. Implementation: `src/command-transaction.ts` exports `CommandTransaction<TEventMap>` class plus `TransactionResult` and `TransactionPrecondition` types. Internal mutation buffer is a discriminated union (`{ kind, ...payload }`). Each builder method `assertPending` + buffers entry + returns `this` for chaining. `commit()` short-circuits on first failed precondition (no mutations or events applied), otherwise replays mutations through the corresponding public `World` API (`setComponent`/`removeComponent`/etc.) so they get the same liveness/JSON-compat validation as direct calls, then emits buffered events through `EventBus`. `abort()` flips state to `aborted`; subsequent `commit()` returns `{ ok: false, code: 'aborted' }`. Single-use: after commit/abort transition, builder methods throw and second commit throws.
